('5','greece','rhodes','/images/rhodes.jpg','My husband and I visited Rhodes this June. We had a very good time and were very impressed by the capital and by the quantity and beauty of the beaches.We had booked a superb studio which was right in the heart of the medieval capital, in a wonderful house.
 So we had all the time to wonder in the narrow streets of the City of Rhodes and admire the complexity and wonders of the medieval architecture; we were told that this city is the biggest medieval city of Europe and I am sure it is one of the most well preserved too.
Apart from the capital, which were our favourite place, we visited some very picturesque mountain villages, admired the rich and varied landscape of the island and relaxed on the golden sand of many endless beaches.
I recommend to everyone to go and discover the richness and charms of Rhodes.'
